{"questionId":"20742","questionHtml":"<p>exactly three&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis intercepts.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;will have three&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis intercepts if</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>c</mi><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;(or equivalent reasoning)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>reasoning from the results in both parts (e)(i) and (e)(ii) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"20742","referenceCode":"21M.3.AHL.TZ1.1e.iii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"exactly three x-axis intercepts.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"e.iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.8—Testing for max and min, optimisation. Points of inflexion"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}